source_id: STP1132-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_9th Volume_011_chunk5
evidence_span: Changes in the crystallographic texture were studied as a function of tensile deformation along the rolling and transverse directions of the sheet

source_id: STP1132-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_9th Volume_011_chunk5
evidence_span: rolling direction deformation seems to cause only little texture reorientations

source_id: STP1132-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_9th Volume_011_chunk5

source_id: STP1132-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_9th Volume_011_chunk6
evidence_span: Mechanical properties and microstructure of $Z \mathbf { r } { \mathbf { - } } \mathbf { S } \mathbf { n }$ binary (0.5 to $8 \mathrm { w t } \%$ Sn) alloys were investigated in both $\beta$ -quenched and tempered conditions.

source_id: STP1132-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_9th Volume_011_chunk6
evidence_span: The yield and ultimate tensile stresses and the percentage elongation were evaluated as a function of tin content, $C$ in both $\beta$ -quenched and tempered $Z _ { \bar { \bf { r } } } . \mathsf { S } _ { \bar { \bf { n } } }$ alloys.
property_name: yield stress, ultimate tensile stress, percentage elongation

source_id: STP1132-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_9th Volume_011_chunk6
evidence_span: The $0 . 2 \%$ yield stress shows a linear relationship with $C ^ { 2 / 3 }$ , suggesting the operation of the Mott-Nabarro model of solid solution strengthening in which clustering of solute atoms is envisaged.

source_id: STP1132-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_9th Volume_011_chunk6
evidence_span: The presence of tin solute clusters could also be detected in TEM microstructures of $\beta$ -quenched alloys.

source_id: STP1132-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_9th Volume_011_chunk6
evidence_span: The effect of tin content on the yield and flow behavior of zirconium has been examined at temperatures between 77 and $6 7 3 \mathrm { ~ \AA ~ }$ .

source_id: STP1132-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_9th Volume_011_chunk6
evidence_span: Results indicate that the addition of tin influenced both the thermal and athermal components of flow stress.

source_id: STP1132-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_9th Volume_011_chunk6
evidence_span: The activation volume was found to be independent of the plastic strain, while it showed an increase with temperature and a decrease with solute content.

source_id: STP1132-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_9th Volume_011_chunk6
evidence_span: The deformation process appeared to be controlled by two ratecontrolling mechanisms: $( a )$ dislocations overcoming the substitutional solute clusters at temperatures below $4 7 3 \mathrm { K }$ , and $( b )$ movement of jogged screw dislocations at higher temperatures.

source_id: STP1132-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_9th Volume_011_chunk6
evidence_span: The intermetallic precipitate phase formed due to tempering was identified as $Z _ { \mathrm { { I } } _ { 3 } } \mathrm { { S n } }$ with A15 structure

source_id: STP1132-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_9th Volume_011_chunk6
evidence_span: Because of the good lattice registry between the precipitate and the matrix phases, partial coherency between them is maintained even after considerable growth of precipitate particles.
